WEBVTT

00:10.580 --> 00:11.460
CHAPTER VI.

00:11.700 --> 00:13.180
HOW RICHES COME TO YOU

00:13.960 --> 00:19.140
When I say that you do not have to drive sharp bargains, I do not mean that you do not have

00:19.140 --> 00:23.820
to drive any bargains at all, or that you are above the necessity for having any dealings

00:23.820 --> 00:24.980
with your fellow men.

00:25.400 --> 00:28.500
I mean that you will not need to deal with them unfairly.

00:28.500 --> 00:33.500
You do not have to get something for nothing, but can give to every man more than you take

00:33.500 --> 00:34.080
from him.

00:34.500 --> 00:39.120
You cannot give every man more in cash market value than you take from him, but you can

00:39.120 --> 00:43.120
give him more in use value than the cash value of the thing you take from him.

00:43.660 --> 00:48.400
The paper, ink, and other material in this book may not be worth the money you pay for

00:48.400 --> 00:48.700
it.

00:49.040 --> 00:54.160
But if the ideas suggested in it bring you thousands of dollars, you have not been wrong

00:54.160 --> 00:55.740
by those who sold it to you.

00:55.740 --> 00:59.320
They have given you a great use value for a small cash value.

01:00.120 --> 01:05.120
Let us suppose that I own a picture by one of the greatest artists, which in any civilized

01:05.120 --> 01:07.840
community is worth thousands of dollars.

01:08.300 --> 01:13.660
I take it to Baffin Bay, and by salesmanship induce an Eskimo to give a bundle of furs

01:13.660 --> 01:15.360
worth five hundred for it.

01:15.700 --> 01:18.900
I have really wronged him, for he has no use for the picture.

01:19.260 --> 01:20.940
It has no use value to him.

01:21.160 --> 01:22.860
It will not add to his life.

01:23.460 --> 01:27.820
But suppose I give him a gun worth fifty dollars for his furs.

01:28.560 --> 01:30.240
Then he has made a good bargain.

01:30.900 --> 01:32.160
He has use for the gun.

01:32.420 --> 01:34.940
It will get him many more furs and much food.

01:35.480 --> 01:37.340
It will add to his life in every day.

01:37.740 --> 01:38.940
It will make him rich.

01:39.760 --> 01:44.160
When you rise from the competitive to the creative plane, you can scan your business

01:44.160 --> 01:49.080
transactions very strictly, and if you are selling any man anything, which does not add

01:49.080 --> 01:53.600
more to his life than the thing he give you in exchange, you can afford to stop it.

01:54.420 --> 01:56.660
You do not have to beat anybody in business.

01:57.100 --> 02:01.280
And if you are in a business which does beat people, get out of it at once.

02:02.240 --> 02:06.380
Give every man more in use value than you take from him in cash value.

02:07.000 --> 02:10.480
Then you are adding to the life of the world by every business transaction.

02:11.500 --> 02:16.100
If you have people working for you, you must take from them more cash value than you pay

02:16.100 --> 02:16.880
them in wages.

02:17.480 --> 02:22.360
But you can so organize your business that it will be filled with the principle of advancement,

02:22.780 --> 02:27.120
and so that each employee who wishes to do so may advance a little every day.

02:27.740 --> 02:31.860
You can make your business do for your employees what this book is doing for you.

02:32.360 --> 02:36.880
You can so conduct your business that it will be a sort of ladder, by which every employee

02:36.880 --> 02:41.900
who will take the trouble may climb to riches himself, and given the opportunity, if he

02:41.900 --> 02:44.020
will not do so, it is not your fault.

02:44.680 --> 02:49.060
And finally, because you are to cause the creation of your riches from formless substance

02:49.060 --> 02:53.260
which permeates all your environment, it does not follow that they are to take shape from

02:53.260 --> 02:55.960
the atmosphere and come into being before your eyes.

02:56.780 --> 03:01.200
If you want a sewing machine, for instance, I do not mean to tell you that you are to

03:01.200 --> 03:05.220
impress the thought of a sewing machine on thinking substance until the machine is formed

03:05.220 --> 03:07.880
without hands, in the room where you sit or elsewhere.

03:08.420 --> 03:12.640
But if you want a sewing machine, hold the mental image of it with the most positive

03:12.640 --> 03:15.820
certainty that it is being made, or is on its way to you.

03:16.420 --> 03:21.460
After once forming the thought, have the most absolute and unquestioning faith that a sewing

03:21.460 --> 03:22.380
machine is coming.

03:22.780 --> 03:27.400
Never think of it, or speak of it, in any other way than as being sure to arrive.

03:27.680 --> 03:29.200
Claim it as already yours.

03:29.980 --> 03:34.560
It will be brought to you by the power of the supreme intelligence acting upon the minds

03:34.560 --> 03:35.180
of men.

03:35.600 --> 03:40.460
If you live in Maine, it may be that a man will be brought from Texas or Japan to engage

03:40.460 --> 03:44.120
in some transaction which will result in your getting what you want.

03:44.640 --> 03:49.680
If so, the whole matter will be as much to that man's advantage as it is to yours.

03:50.360 --> 03:55.120
Do not forget for a moment that the thinking substance is through all, in all, communicating

03:55.120 --> 03:57.240
with all, and can influence all.

03:57.540 --> 04:02.260
The desire of thinking substance for fuller life and better living has caused the creation

04:02.260 --> 04:07.160
of all the sewing machines already made, and this can cause the creation of millions more,

04:07.160 --> 04:12.420
and will, whenever men set it in motion by desire and faith, and by acting in a certain

04:12.420 --> 04:12.880
way.

04:13.580 --> 04:18.360
You can certainly have a sewing machine in your house, and it is just as certain that

04:18.360 --> 04:23.240
you can have any other thing or things which you want, and which you will use for the advancement

04:23.240 --> 04:25.480
of your own life and the lives of others.

04:26.220 --> 04:28.520
You need not hesitate about asking largely.

04:28.880 --> 04:32.280
It is your father's pleasure to give you the kingdom, said Jesus.

04:33.240 --> 04:37.620
Original substance wants to live all that is possible in you, and wants you to have

04:37.620 --> 04:41.660
all that you can or will use for the living of the most abundant life.

04:42.400 --> 04:46.760
If you fix upon your consciousness the fact that the desire you feel for the possession

04:46.760 --> 04:52.260
of riches is one with the desire for omnipotence for more complete expression, your faith becomes

04:52.260 --> 04:52.940
invincible.

04:53.900 --> 04:58.920
Once, I saw a little boy sitting at a piano, and vainly trying to bring harmony out of

04:58.920 --> 05:04.120
the keys, and I saw that he was grieved and provoked by his inability to play real music.

05:04.640 --> 05:07.880
I asked him the cause of this vexation, and he answered,

05:08.280 --> 05:11.920
I can feel the music in me, but I can't make my hands go right.

05:12.440 --> 05:16.880
The music in him was the urge of original substance, containing all the possibilities

05:16.880 --> 05:17.740
of all life.

05:18.120 --> 05:21.560
All that there is of music was seeking expression through the child.

05:22.280 --> 05:27.040
God, the one substance, is trying to live and do and enjoy things through humanity.

05:27.040 --> 05:33.300
He is saying, I want hands to build wonderful structures, to play divine harmonies, to paint

05:33.300 --> 05:34.400
glorious pictures.

05:34.920 --> 05:40.320
I want feet to run my errands, eyes to see my beauties, tongues to tell mighty truths,

05:40.740 --> 05:43.300
and to sing marvelous songs, and so on.

05:44.060 --> 05:47.520
All that there is of possibility is seeking expression through men.

05:48.000 --> 05:52.960
God wants those who can play music to have pianos and every other instrument, and to

05:52.960 --> 05:56.160
have the means to cultivate their talents to the fullest extent.

05:56.560 --> 06:00.780
He wants those who can appreciate beauty to be able to surround themselves with beautiful

06:00.780 --> 06:01.320
things.

06:01.740 --> 06:06.380
He wants those who can discern the truth to have every opportunity to travel and observe.

06:06.920 --> 06:11.260
He wants those who can appreciate dress to be beautifully clothed, and those who can

06:11.260 --> 06:13.980
appreciate good food to be luxuriously fed.

06:14.700 --> 06:18.960
He wants all these things, because it is himself that enjoys and appreciates them.

06:19.240 --> 06:24.400
It is God who wants to play, and sing, and enjoy beauty, and proclaim truth, and wear

06:24.400 --> 06:26.360
fine clothes, and eat good foods.

06:26.840 --> 06:30.740
It is God that worketh in you to will and to do, said Paul.

06:31.380 --> 06:37.060
The desire you feel for riches is the infinite seeking to express himself in you, as he sought

06:37.060 --> 06:39.780
to find expression in the little boy at the piano.

06:40.520 --> 06:42.780
So you need not hesitate to ask largely.

06:43.520 --> 06:46.900
Your part is to focalize and express the desire to God.

06:47.720 --> 06:50.020
This is a difficult point with most people.

06:50.020 --> 06:55.300
They retain something of the old idea that poverty and self-sacrifice are pleasing to

06:55.300 --> 06:55.560
God.

06:56.120 --> 07:00.100
They look upon poverty as a part of the plan, a necessity of nature.

07:00.780 --> 07:05.880
They have the idea that God has finished his work, and made all that he can make, and that

07:05.880 --> 07:09.900
the majority of men must stay poor, because there is not enough to go around.

07:10.460 --> 07:15.280
They hold so much to this erroneous thought that they feel ashamed to ask for wealth.

07:15.700 --> 07:20.440
They try not to want more than a very modest competence, just enough to make them fairly

07:20.440 --> 07:21.080
comfortable.

07:21.680 --> 07:26.700
I recall now a case of one student who was told that he must get in mind a clear picture

07:26.700 --> 07:31.480
of the things he desired, so that the creative thought of them might be impressed on formless

07:31.480 --> 07:32.080
substance.

07:32.580 --> 07:37.240
He was a very poor man, living in a rented house, and having only what he earned from

07:37.240 --> 07:41.340
day to day, and he could not grasp the fact that all wealth was his.

07:42.000 --> 07:47.580
So, after thinking the matter over, he decided that he might reasonably ask for a new rug

07:47.580 --> 07:52.800
on the floor of his best room, and an anthracite coal-stove, to heat the house during the cold

07:52.800 --> 07:53.220
winter.

07:53.760 --> 07:58.140
Following the instructions given in this book, he obtained these things in a few months,

07:58.440 --> 08:01.300
and that it dawned upon him that he had not asked enough.

08:01.760 --> 08:05.820
He went through the house in which he lived, and planned all the improvements he would

08:05.820 --> 08:06.800
like to make in it.

08:06.800 --> 08:11.940
He mentally added a bay window here, a room there, until it was complete in his mind as

08:11.940 --> 08:15.560
his ideal home, and then he planned its furnishings.

08:15.820 --> 08:20.340
Holding the whole picture in his mind, he began living in the certain way, and moving

08:20.340 --> 08:21.540
toward what he wanted.

08:21.980 --> 08:26.460
And he owns the house now, and is rebuilding it after the form of his mental image.

08:26.700 --> 08:31.040
And now, with still larger faith, he is going on to get greater things.

08:31.040 --> 08:36.580
It has been unto him according to his faith, and it is so with you and with all of us.

